                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.C001/825a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chairman of the American Delegation</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davis</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-10-14T10:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 14, 1933—10 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>376. Assuming you have not already done so, please telegraph an analysis of the
                    reaction at the League to the reported German withdrawal and an analysis of the
                    implications of this move on European political developments as you see
                    them.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
